
# Flight Booking Simulator With Dynamic Pricing

This project is a web-based flight booking simulator that mimics real-world airline systems. It features a dynamic pricing engine that adjusts ticket prices based on demand, time of day, and seat availability. Built for developers and learners, the simulator demonstrates how pricing algorithms and booking flows work in modern travel applications.
üéØ Key Highlights
- Dynamic Pricing Logic: Prices fluctuate based on demand level, booking time, and remaining inventory
- Multi-step Booking Flow: Includes flight selection, passenger details, price confirmation, and receipt generation
- PNR Generation: Each booking generates a unique Passenger Name Record
- Receipt Download: Users can download a detailed receipt after booking
- Responsive UI: Built with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript , optimized for desktop and mobile
üí° Use Cases
- Educational demo for pricing algorithms
- Frontend development practice with real-world features
- Prototype for travel tech applications


## Features

- Dynamic Pricing Engine: Prices adjust based on seat availability, demand, and time to departure.
- Multi-Step Booking Flow: Includes flight selection, passenger details, payment simulation, and confirmation.
- PNR Generation: Unique Passenger Name Record (PNR) created for each booking.
- Receipt Download: Generates and downloads a PDF receipt post-booking.
- Responsive UI: Clean, mobile-friendly interface with intuitive navigation.
- LocalStorage Integration: Persists booking data across sessions.
- Mock API Backend: Simulates real-time flight data and booking endpoints.

