## Dynamic Pricing Logic

This module implements a dynamic pricing algorithm for a flight booking app. Prices adjust in real-time based on demand, time of day, and remaining inventory.
üîß How It Works
The pricing function takes four inputs:
- basePrice: The starting price of the ticket
- demandLevel: "low", "medium", or "high"
- timeOfDay: Hour of the day (0‚Äì23)
- inventoryLeft: Number of seats remaining

## Booking flow

This simulator guides users through a multi-step flight booking process, mimicking real-world airline systems. Each step is modular and interactive, ensuring a smooth user experience.
üõí Step-by-Step Booking Flow
- Flight Selection
- User selects origin, destination, date, and preferred flight
- Dynamic pricing is applied based on demand, time, and inventory
- Passenger Details
- Form to enter passenger name, age, gender, and contact info
- Validation ensures all required fields are completed
- Price Confirmation
- Final price is displayed with breakdown (base + dynamic adjustments)
- Option to go back and modify flight or passenger details
- Booking Confirmation
- Unique PNR (Passenger Name Record) is generated
- Booking details are saved locally or sent to backend (if integrated)
- Receipt Generation
- A downloadable receipt is created with flight and passenger info
- Includes timestamp, PNR, and total fare

